Ah ok, that makes more sense.  The history UI just displays what was recorded as the user on application start event from spark.  In the case the daemons are running as user yarn without security it appears this is being put in as user yarn:

{"Event":"SparkListenerApplicationStart","App Name":"JavaWordCount","Timestamp":1402600427658,"User":"yarn"}

I'm a little bit surprised that the change you made fixes that for multiple users.  is SPARK_USER set to your user when you start the history server?  Does it work with multiple users?  We should probably change it to put the correct user in the event log.  Or perhaps your change is fixing it so that it gets logs properly?
